Title: Oscar Klein and Gauge Theory

Comments: A talk delivered at the Oscar Klein Centenary Symposium, 46 pages

plus 1 uuencoded eps figuresIn this talk, delivered at the Oscar Klein Centenary Symposium in Stockholm,I review the 1938 conference held in Warsaw devoted to \lq \lq New Theories inPhysics". I review all of the talks presented at this meeting and discuss indetail Klein's paper where he proposed a unified model of electromagnetism andthe nuclear force that foreshadowed the later developments of non-Abelian gaugetheories.